<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency in Huancabamba Extended </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State of Emergency in Huancabamba Extended </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2204200494 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2204200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Ministry extended the state of emergency in 
Huancabamba Province, Piura Department, for another 60 days to 
facilitate the implementation of counterterrorism operations in 
this region of the country. 
  In view of this, civil rights such as the inviolability of 
residences, election of place of residence, the right to hold 
peaceful gatherings without guns, and the right of not being 
arrested without a court warrant are suspended. 
  According to the supreme government decree published today 
in 
the official newspaper EL PERUANO, the Armed Forces will 
guarantee the control of internal order in keeping with the 
established law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

