<H3> <TI>   Cienfuegos Generator Breakdown Causes New Outages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cienfuegos Generator Breakdown Causes New Outages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2204235894 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2204235894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, Unit No. 4 of the Carlos Manuel de 
Cespedes power plant in Cienfuegos, with a generating capacity 
of 158 megawatts, had to be taken offline due to a rupture in 
one of the unit's boiler pipes. This situation will cause 
greater outage problems than those that took place over the past 
weekend. 
  Jorge Carballo of the Electric Union pointed out that this 
unit should be repaired within the next 72 hours. He added that 
workers are now waiting for the boiler to cool down to begin 
repairs. When this unit goes back into service, units No. 1 of 
Santa Cruz del Norte and No. 6 of Diez de Octubre will be taken 
offline for maintenance. 

</TEXT>

