<H3> <TI>   Cienfuegos Mills Increase Electric Self-Sufficiency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cienfuegos Mills Increase Electric Self-Sufficiency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2304164994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2304164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cienfuegos Province sugar mills have attained, 
during the current phase [of the harvest], 83.2 percent of the 
plan for self-sufficiency in electrical energy. This is some 2.6 
percent more than in the same period in 1993. Scheduled repairs 
to the sugar installations are designed to restore the areas 
that generate steam and to relocate four turbogenerators to 
provide an emergency reserve of 3.6 megawatts. 

</TEXT>

