<H3> <TI>   Lack of Refrigeration Affects Alcohol Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lack of Refrigeration Affects Alcohol Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2504151994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1404 GMT 
25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2504151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A lack of ice and refrigeration at the distillery of 
the Jesus Rabi Sugar Mill in Calimete Municipality, Matanzas 
Province, is destabilizing part of the technological process of 
production at that mill. Because of the lack of climate control, 
it is not possible to maintain the stocks necessary to the 
process. This also negatively affects the quality of the 
different kinds of alcohol. Factory technicians say the 
refrigeration problem has been public and under discussion and 
analysis since January, when the work of that (?factory) began. 
  This problem has affected industrial efficiency in 
fermentation as well as the mill's alcohol-producing work group, 
on whom guaranteeing the quality of the product does not depend. 
[sentence as heard] The product is a traditional one that has 
many uses and is also exported. 

</TEXT>

