demanding the return of the president; and a total embargo, but 
not the kind of embargo that is a source of suffering. To 
respect the Haitian people is to agree not to impose what they 
have rejected. We have rejected this kind of embargo by 
requesting a total embargo. May the desires of the Haitian 
people be respected. [end recording] 
