<H3> <TI>   Castro Invites Emigres to Reception </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro Invites Emigres to Reception </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2404210694 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 2028 GMT 24 Apr 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2404210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Javier Rodriguez] </F>
  [Text] Havana, 24 Apr (PL) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro 
will hold a reception for the Cubans living abroad who are 
participating here in The Nation and the Emigrants Conference, 
Miguel Alfonso, spokesman for the meeting, confirmed today. 
  The Cuban president invited the 215 emigrants from 29 
countries to a reception following the closing session of the 
meeting that began on 22 April on an initiative by the Cuban 
Foreign Ministry. 
  Alfonso confirmed the invitation during a meeting with the 
press, during which he reported on the participation of Vice 
President Carlos Lage, who spoke about the current economic 
situation and the country's outlook, which has worsened with the 
disappearance of the European socialist bloc and the tightening 
of the U.S. economic blockade. 
  According to Alfonso, Lage said the Cuban emigrants will not 
be kept from investing in the island, but said that future 
meetings will determine the mechanisms that will be applied in 
that regard. 

</TEXT>

