<H3> <TI>   Castro Meets Conference Participants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro Meets Conference Participants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2504063294 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0543 GMT 25 Apr 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2504063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 25 Apr (PL) -- President Fidel Castro 
welcomed the 225 participants in the "The Nation and the 
Emigrants" conference, greeting them personally one by one. 
  The weekly TRABAJADORES magazine reports today that the 
Cuban 
leader thanked the emigres during the meeting last night for 
their "solidarity and presence in the fatherland, for their 
expressions of support for Cuba, for preserving the achievements 
of the revolution, and for our people and their continuous, 
tremendous struggle against the U.S. Government's blockade." 
  The weekly notes in a short article that Carlos Lage, 
secretary of the executive committee and vice president of the 
Council of State; Foreign Affairs Minister Roberto Robaina; 
Ricardo Alarcon, president of the National Assembly of the 
People's Government; Abel Prieto, president of the National 
Union of Cuban Writers and Artists; and Jose Ramon Balaguer, all 
of whom are members of the Politburo of the Communist Party of 
Cuba, participated in the meeting with Fidel Castro. 

</TEXT>

