<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Castillo Expelled From PNC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castillo Expelled From PNC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20675C </F>
<F P=103> 94P20675C </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua BARRICADA in Spanish of 9 April 
1994 on page 8 reports that Edmundo Castillo has been expelled 
from the National Conservative Party, PNC, for one year because 
he does not follow the party line. The article explains that 
Castillo, who is renowned for his oratory skills in the National 
Assembly, has a reputation for being "very independent." 
Castillo explained that he was expelled because he supported 
constitutional reforms and because he criticized the party for 
practicing nepotism and for only representing a single class of 
society. 

</TEXT>

