<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increased Fishing Sector Investments Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increased Fishing Sector Investments Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20675B </F>
<F P=103> 94P20675B </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua LA TRIBUNA in Spanish of 11 
April 1994 on page 8B reports that the Nicafish and Pananica 
enterprises signed a $6.15 million investment agreement with the 
Ministry of Economy and Development. The two enterprises, which 
have Panamanian assets, are involved in fishing and processing 
seafood in San Juan del Sur. According to the article, Pananica 
will invest $4.15 million to purchase 15 fishing boats and hire 
85 employees. The remaining $2 million will be invested by 
Nicafish, which was recently taken over by the National 
Corporation of the Public Sector. The article explains that the 
government hopes seafood exports will range between $40 and $65 
million in 1994, compared to $32 million last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

