<F P=100> CENTRAL AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calderon Sol To Comply With Peace Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calderon Sol To Comply With Peace Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2604020394 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU in Spanish 1800 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2604020394 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "YSU Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Today, Salvadoran Foreign Minister Miguel Angel 
Salaverria said future president Armando Calderon Sol, the 
winner of the 25 April elections, will comply fully with 
commitments that remain pending from the peace agreements. The 
peace agreements, signed two years ago, put an end to the bloody 
civil war in this Central American nation. In an interview with 
the media, Salaverria noted that no one can ignore an 
international agreement involving the international community, 
represented by the United Nations, because to lie to or ignore 
the United Nations is a very serious offense. Salaverria added 
that Calderon Sol has already committed himself to fully comply 
with any issues pending from the peace agreements signed with 
the guerrillas. 
  After declaring himself the winner of the elections on 
Sunday 
night, Calderon indicated that his first mission will be to 
consolidate peace, and in doing so, he will begin a dialogue 
with the opposition represented by the former guerrilla movement 
Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front, among other political 
forces. 
  Calderon Sol also announced that he will travel to New York 
in May, when he will meet with UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali to discuss the peace process and convey his 
intention of fulfilling the commitments of the peace agreements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

