<H3> <TI>   Foreign Relations Minister Arrives in Bonn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Relations Minister Arrives in Bonn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2504184494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1620 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2504184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, 24 Apr (EFE) -- Bolivian Foreign Minister 
Antonio Aranibar Quiroga arrived in Bonn on 24 April. He will 
spend three days in Germany during which he will sign a 
financial cooperation agreement worth 650 million marks ($380 
million). 
  Aranibar Quiroga's official agenda will begin on 25 April: 
He 
will meet with his German counterpart Klaus Kinkel, Hans-Peter 
Repnik, secretary of state of the Ministry for Economic 
Cooperation [title as received], and many businessmen and 
politicians. 
  On 26 April he will hold several political meetings, attend 
a 
luncheon hosted by the chairman of the Federal Parliament 
Foreign Relations Committee, hold a news conference, and depart 
for Berlin. 
  The Bolivian Foreign Minister will conclude his visit on 27 
April in Hamburg where he will meet with Senate Speaker Henning 
Voscherau. Before departing for Madrid, he will visit the South 
American German Bank and the Ibero-American Association. 

</TEXT>

