<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Currency To Be Introduced on 1 July </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Currency To Be Introduced on 1 July </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2504223394 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 24 
Apr 94 Section 1 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY2504223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Based on the latest data collected by the research 
institutes, the Finance Ministry has concluded that prices 
converted into Real Value Units (URV's) rose by 5 percent 
between March and April. This has prompted the government to 
implement the real on 1 July. 
  Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero's team believes the 
decision 
to introduce the real in July and to announce its implementation 
35 days in advance will give the economic agents more security 
and reduce price readjustments. 
  The Finance Ministry attributes the increase in prices after 
they were converted into URV to entrepreneurs' fear of an 
eventual price control and of a freeze on the basic foodstuff 
basket produce. 
  The inflation in URV has made Ricupero give up the idea of 
implementing the real on 1 June. 

</TEXT>

