<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori: Old Rules Guarantee Clean Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujimori: Old Rules Guarantee Clean Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2504180194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1709 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2504180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Lima, 23 Apr (EFE) -- Peruvian President 
Alberto Fujimori asserted that now that Congress has approved 
the proposal that the National Elections Board (JNE) organize 
the elections, nobody can suspect any fraud. [passage omitted] 
  Fujimori on 22 April told journalists in Arequipa, 1,000 km 
south of Lima, that with this decision "now absolutely nobody 
can question the clear and transparent development of the 
electoral process." 
  He added that reports stating that "the government upheld 
electoral fraud" have thus been dismissed, and said the 
executive branch will not have any problem promulgating the law 
approved by Congress. 
  Fujimori indirectly referred to the possible presidential 
candidacy of former UN Secretary General Javier Perez de Cuellar 
by stating: "The road is clear and nobody can condition his 
candidacy to the establishment of clear and clean rules." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

