she 
held a protocol meeting with President Fujimori with the 
objective of strengthening bilateral ties. 
  Before leaving Government House, she observed the 
traditional 
changing of the guard conducted by the Junin guard detachment at 
the Honor Patio. 
  [Second unidentified reporter] In the afternoon, Colombian 
Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin de Rubio left the Foreign Ministry 
building to place a wreath at the Simon Bolivar monument at 
Congress Plaza. 
  [Noemi Sanin de Rubio] We will install the neighborhood 
committees [comisiones de vencidad]. We will hold meetings and 
meet with the media. With President Fujimori, we will open a 
new school. We strive to achieve integration not only at the 
government level but also at all social levels. [end recording] 

