<H3> <TI>   Castro Chairs Talks With Zambian Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro Chairs Talks With Zambian Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2704001394 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2220 GMT 
26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2704001394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The official talks between Cuba and Zambia began 
today at the Palace of the Revolution. The meetings are being 
chaired by Commander in Chief Fidel Castro, head of state and 
government, and by Zambian President Frederick Chiluba. 
  Minutes prior to the conversations, Frederick Chiluba 
honored 
our National hero Jose Marti, accompanied by Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina. From today, through 30 April when they 
leave, the Zambian delegation is scheduled to meet with 
representatives of the scientific-technical field and other 
areas of social, economic, and cultural interest. 
  Zambia, a country of the southern African cone, is seven 
times larger than Cuba, with a population of approximately 9 
million. Its principal export is copper. 

</TEXT>

