<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Coast Guard Repatriates 98 Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Coast Guard Repatriates 98 Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2604181194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2604181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Almost 100 Haitian boat people were repatriated on 
25 April to Port-au-Prince by a U.S. Coast Guard patrol ship 
that intercepted them. The 98 refugees, who were trying to reach 
Florida on board a makeshift boat, were intercepted on 22 April 
in the Windward Passage between Haiti and Cuba. The boat people, 
including three children without parents, sailed from the island 
of La Tortue. 
  It should be recalled that on Saturday, 95 Haitians, 
survivors of a shipwreck on an island of the Bahamas, were 
repatriated by plane from the Bahamas to Port-au-Prince. 

</TEXT>

