<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Diego Fernandez de Cevallos, presidential candidate 
for the National Action Party [PAN], is in Chiapas, where he 
commented on the debate. 
  [Begin Fernandez de Cevallos recording] I believe Dr. 
Zedillo 
suggested the three main parties hold the first debate. I, 
however, am willing to attend debates with the other candidates. 
We all have the right to participate. It would be practically 
impossible to have all the candidates in the same place at the 
same time, but I am open to the idea, and the other candidates 
will find that I am very willing to participate with them in 
many debates. Perhaps we can soon set dates to debate national 
issues and our political proposals with other candidates. [end 
recording] 
  [Further on in the same newscast, there is a recording of 
Institutional Revolutionary Candidate Ernesto Zedillo responding 
to Fernandez de Cevallos' acceptance of the debate invitation: 
"I am very pleased to know that a least one of the candidates I 
invited to this debate has responded in the most constructive 
manner possible. He has even suggested a date, 3 May, and a 
debate format. This encourages me, and I would like to tell the 
candidate who answered my invitation that I accept the date he 
suggested."] 

