<H3> <TI>   TSE Initiates Final Presidential Vote Count </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TSE Initiates Final Presidential Vote Count </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2604195494 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU in Spanish 1800 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2604195494 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "YSU Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The TSE [Supreme Electoral Tribunal] has initiated 
the final vote count of 24 April's presidential election, which 
Dr. Armando Calderon Sol of ARENA [Nationalist Republican 
Alliance] won in a contest against the left-wing coalition. 
  ARENA won 68.27 percent of the valid votes, and the 
coalition 
won 31.68 percent [figures as heard], the equivalent of more 
than 803,000 votes for the right-wing party and 367,000 for the 
left-wing party. 
  The TSE has announced that within the next five days it will 
disclose the final results of the elections, which determined 
who will govern the country from 1994 to 1999. 

</TEXT>

