<H3> <TI>   Croatian Official Arrives for Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian Official Arrives for Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2704174994 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2704174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic arrived today 
in the country for a 48-hour official visit. He will meet 
President Carlos Menem and Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella. 
  Granic is the first Croatian official to visit Argentina 
since the establishing of diplomatic relations between the two 
countries. 
  Granic also will sign the first overall cooperation 
agreement 
with his Argentine colleague, and he will discuss a bilateral 
agreement regarding the drafting of an agenda containing topics 
of common interest. 

</TEXT>

