<H3> <TI>   Eduardo Menem Reelected Senate President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eduardo Menem Reelected Senate President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2704024494 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2153 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2704024494 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 26 Apr (NA) -- The Senate this 
afternoon reelected Justicialist Party [PJ] Senator Eduardo 
Menem for the sixth consecutive time as provisional Senate 
president, and confirmed PJ Senator Oraldo Britos as Senate vice 
president. 
  The Senate unanimously elected Rio Negro UCR [Radical Civic 
Union] Senator Faustino Mazzucco as Senate first vice president, 
and Neuquen Popular Movement (MPN) Senator Jorge Solana as 
Senate second vice president. 
  The elections involving the four posts took barely 20 
minutes 
during a session to which Presidential Secretary General Eduardo 
Bauza, former Interior Minister Julio Mera Figueroa, and 
Institutional Affairs Secretary Liliana Gurdulich de Correa had 
been specially invited. 

</TEXT>

