  [Text] Buenos Aires, 27 Apr (NA) -- Another arrest was 
made at midnight by the Buenos Aires Province Police in the 
investigation San Isidro Federal Judge Roberto Marquevich is 
carrying out into the discovery of a powerful arms cache on an 
island in the Tigre District. 
  According to court sources, the arrested person has been 
identified as Daniel Sinaglia and, as in the case of Alejandro 
Sucksdorf, he carried out intelligence activities for the Army. 
  Sinaglia's arrest was made at midnight in the town of San 
Fernando, according to sources close to Judge Marquevich. 

