<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Cites Position on UN Population Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Cites Position on UN Population Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2604214994 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2604214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chile has established its position on the UN 
Population and Development Conference to be held in September. 
Pope John Paul II has already criticized this conference. 
  Sernam [National Women's Secretariat] Director Josefina 
Bilbao explained Chile's position on this conference which will 
be held in Cairo. 
  She explained that, during the conference, Chile will 
express 
its opposition to abortion, an issue that will be discussed and 
which has been harshly criticized by Pope John Paul II. But the 
Chilean position differs from that of the Vatican in that it 
upholds that there is more than one type of family. 
  Bilbao said that the National Family Council believes this 
concept also encompasses common-law marriages and single-parent 
families. She added that Chile supports birth control, which 
has been practiced in our country for the past 30 years. 

</TEXT>

