<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori Forces Foreign TV Cameraman To Erase Film </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujimori Forces Foreign TV Cameraman To Erase Film </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2604213194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1551 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2604213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 26 Apr (EFE) -- Peruvian President Alberto 
Fujimori has personally forced a cameraman from a foreign 
television station to erase part of the film he took of women 
inmates during a visit made by Fujimori to a Peruvian prison. 
  The Association of Foreign Journalists in Peru (APEP) said 
in 
a communique released today that this event "is an isolated act 
of censorship against freedom of the press, which should not be 
allowed to be repeated." The communique adds that the cameraman 
"was forced by the president himself to erase part of the film 
taken during his visit" to the prison for terrorists in 
Yanamayo, Puno Department, at the Bolivian border. 
  According to the communique, the film that was erased 
includes footage of a group of women inmates, who read a 
document related to their situation in the presence of the 
visitors. The communique says "the correspondents and the world 
were thus deprived of information of public interest, when there 
was not even a warning of any restrictions" on the 
correspondents who visited the prison. 

</TEXT>

