<F P=103> PA2804012094 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ligia Moreno and Aneris Gonzalez from "The News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] [Moreno] The economic cabinet of President Rafael 
Caldera today announced the general strategy or guidelines of 
the economic plan to be implemented over the next five years. 
One of the highlights is that Venezuelan Petroleum will give 10 
percent of its shares to its employees. Other major points 
include an emphasis on decentralization and private investments. 
Various sectors support the plan and think President Caldera is 
on the right track. Time will tell, however, and we have to wait 
and see how the economic plan proposed by the Caldera cabinet 
works. 
  [Gonzalez] It is worth mentioning that a large number of 
people from all sectors--namely, CTV [Confederation of 
Venezuelan Workers], Consecomercio [National Council of Commerce 
and Services], and Fedecamaras [Venezuelan Federation of 
Associations and Chambers of Commerce and Industry]--have 
gathered here at the Eurobuilding Hotel, as you can see your 
screen, to discuss and review the entire economic program. As 
you rightly pointed out, Ligia, the opening to private 
investment is one of the highlights of this strategy, and, in 
some way, it has grabbed the attention of all sectors of society. 

</TEXT>

