<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visiting British Investors View Oil Exploration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visiting British Investors View Oil Exploration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2804020694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2804020694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A second British company will probably undertake oil 
exploration projects in Cuba. This news was released today 
during a news conference given by Michael Adda, head of the 
delegation from Caritad, a group which promotes trade with the 
Caribbean. 
  Talks will be held throughout the week among members of the 
Caritad delegation and Cuban representatives, who will discuss 
projects on ways to establish agreements in tourism, 
agriculture, oil exploration, and maritime services. 
  During the news conference it was also reported that the 
British secretary of state for trade and industry and a new 
group of British businessmen will visit Cuba in September. 
  Adda said that some of the proposals submitted by investors 
of this group will be confirmed by the end of this year. He 
added that Great Britain must also contribute to the economic 
recovery of Cuba; we are awaiting with great expectations the 
measures that will probably be adopted by the special Cuban 
legislative session that will be held this week, he said. 
  More than 100 contacts were held over the past few days 
between British and Cuban businessmen. 

</TEXT>

